+# Shipshape Agents
+
+This project uses Shipshape for spec-driven development.
+
+## Project Configuration
+
+See [RIGGING.md](RIGGING.md) for tooling values.
+
+## Stack
+
+- Language: JavaScript
+- Runtime: Node.js
+- Package Manager: npm
+- Test Runner: Cucumber.js
+
+## Directories
+
+- Implementation: `src/` - Production code
+- Specs: `features/` - Gherkin feature files
+- Verification: `features/support/` - Step definitions and test support
+- Assets: `data/` - Test data and content
+
+## Commands
+
+- `npm test`: Run Cucumber.js test suite
+- `npx cucumber-js`: Run Cucumber.js directly
+- `npx cucumber-js --dry-run`: Static discovery (list undefined/unimplemented steps)
+- `npx cucumber-js --format usage`: List step usage
+
+## Verification Tiers
+
+- `@logic`: Default tier for pure local tests (no external dependencies)
+
+## Workflow
+
+1. Captain writes durable specs in `.feature` files
+2. QM runs verification and creates worklist from failing targets
+3. Crew implements smallest production change
+4. Boatswain handles hygiene and local commit custody
+5. Shipwright performs harbour inspection and fitting out
+
+## Harbour Cadence
+
+Shipwright runs between voyages to:
+- Inventory production code
+- Add `@planks(...)` trace annotations
+- Write `@captain` scenario skeletons
+- Remove condemned scenarios and code
+- Audit verification economy
+
+## Current State
+
+This is a tide prediction project with:
+- `src/tide.js`: Production tide prediction logic
+- `features/tides.feature`: Tide prediction scenarios
+- `features/support/steps.js`: Step definitions
+- `data/tides.json`: Tide data for testing
