+# Tidewatch 5
+
+A tide prediction system.
+
+## Shipshape
+
+This repository uses [Shipshape](https://github.com/dmytri/shipshape), a context-isolated spec-driven workflow for coding agents.
+
+### Articles of Agreement
+
+- **Durable artifacts outrank chat**: Binding product behaviour lives in `.feature` files
+- **Current design only**: Specs and code describe the current design
+- **Simplest sufficient change**: One role, one job, smallest useful change
+- **Deferral is not safety**: Push to 100% completion in the fewest possible cycles
+- **Real by default**: Verification exercises real behaviour
+- **Passing verification is not proof**: Passing checks only show that current checks pass
+
+### Roles
+
+- **Captain**: Human-facing discovery, durable specs/assets
+- **QM**: Fresh-context verification and executable coverage
+- **Crew**: Smallest production change for one failing target
+- **Boatswain**: Hygiene, verification recheck, local commit custody
+- **Shipwright**: Harbour code inspection, `@planks(...)` annotations, `@captain` scenarios
+
+### Configuration
+
+See [RIGGING.md](RIGGING.md) and [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for project tooling and workflow details.
+
+## Development
+
+```bash
+npm install
+npm test
+```
+
+## Project Structure
+
+- `src/`: Production code
+- `features/`: Gherkin specifications
+- `features/support/`: Step definitions and test support
+- `data/`: Test data
\ No newline at end of file
